result.execSummary:
The defendant Dalen J Beauprey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Receiving Stolen Property >$5000 - $10,000 or Firearm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.34(1)(bm).
  • Receiving Stolen Property >$5000 - $10,000 or Firearm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.34(1)(bm).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: The restitution must be paid within first six (6) months of probation.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

The defendant may not consume/possess any alcohol.

The defendant may not enter any tavern/bar.

The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must enroll in AODA assessment within 90 days of release from incarceration.

timeConds.notes: Must be completed in the first year of probation.

Defendant Dalen J Beauprey in court, in custody with attorney Amy Lynn Ferguson.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Also called 13CF224. Called 1:52 p.m. 15CF03 - Court has plea questionaire, State G plea to 1 & 2, remaining counts DRI & free to argue on sentence.  Beauprey & Ferguson agree. Court dismisses, but reads in count 3. Defendant pleads G to Count 1 & 2. Court goes over plea questionaire form, court finds defendant has freely, voluntarily and intellegently waived his right to a jury trial, by entering his plea. Court accepts pleas and adjudges guilty. State makes final argument asks for consecutive sentence to revocation, asking for restituition $500 (insurance deductable). Ferguson objects to the restituition for stated reasons. State proceeds with recommendation 13CF224 Counts 1 & 2 - 9 months on each count, concurrent to one another. 84 days jail credit (stipulated). 15CF03 - Count 1 - one year FC jail consecutive to 13CF224, count 2 - with hold sentence and place on probation for 3 years consecutive to count 1. Ferguson has recieved a copy of Revocation for 13CF24 and finds no inaccuracies. Ferguson makes final argument and recommends 13CF224 - time served (84 days). 15CF03 - Count 1 (71 days credit if revoked) Impose and stay, place on probation for 2 years, 3 months conditional jail time, consecutive to 13CF24. Beaupreay makes statement, remorseful. State has complies with victim notification. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 13CF224 - Count 2 - 6 months in FC jail with huber privileges, Count 3 - 6 months concurrent to count 2, credit for 84 days. 15CF03 - Count 1 - Impose & stay 5 years, (2 years incarceration and 3 years extended supervision, stayed and place on probation for 3 years, 6 months FC jail consecutive to 13CF224, Count 2 - same Imposed & stayed sentence, concurrent to count 1, probation conditions, no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into bars/taverns, AODA and follow through (must sign up within first 90 days of release of incarceration), 100 hours community service completed within one year of probation, full time employment with verbage, costs on each count, on case 13CF224 enter civil judgment for unpaid fines, 15CF03 - only restitution ordered is $200 payable to FC Sheriff (undercover buy money) must be paid within first 6 months of probation, DNA surcharges. Court advises of voting, possession firearm rights & postconviction relief.
